<headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 15 at 7:50AM CDT  by NWS Brownsville</headline>
<description>...Areas of Fog Affecting Jim Hogg County...
Surface observations indicate that patchy areas of dense fog have
developed across Jim Hogg County reducing visibilities down into
the 1/2 mile to 1 mile range. These areas of fog are mainly
affecting the Hebbronville. These areas of fog should dissipate
by 9 AM.
Morning motorists traveling through Jim Hogg County are urged to
reduce speed, use low beam headlights, and avoid following other
vehicles too closely in areas of fog through the mid morning
hours.</description>
